For 90 years, Social Security has been a stable and secure retirement guarantee for all Americans. Senate Democrats are standing up against attempts to privatize it.

We are fighting back against efforts to undercut or privatize Social Security.

Our seniors deserve to retire with dignity.
In the face of attacks by the administration, we are fighting back against attempts to cut or privatize Social Security.
Americans have paid into Social Security with every paycheck and count on it for a secure retirement. We’re fighting to protect these hard-earned benefits from attempts to cut them.

Social Security is a lifeline for 74 million Americans.

We shouldn’t privatize it, we should strengthen it.

We should be able to bring high-speed internet to every family in Minnesota — regardless of their zip code. @SenTinaSmith and I secured funding to ensure Pine County receives broadband upgrades so families and businesses can reliably access high-speed internet.

Big Pharma’s abusive patent tactics have long blocked patients from accessing cheaper medicines. The result has meant higher prices & fewer choices. I joined @SenBlumenthal & @JohnCornyn’s bipartisan bill to end some of these practices & restore healthy competition.

Honored to be named a Defender of Children by @Campaign4Kids. From investing in affordable child care and education to protecting kids from unsafe food products, I will never stop fighting for America’s children.

It’s a privilege to receive the Montgomery Medal from the National Guard Association. The men and women of the National Guard put everything on the line when they put on the uniform, and I will continue to work to provide them with the resources they need to keep us safe.

It was great to visit @UMNMorris to meet with Chancellor Janet Schrunk Ericksen and an incredible group of faculty. We stopped by the campus observatory, which I highly recommend to anyone interested in astronomy!

Falls International Airport is a critical hub for communities in Northern Minnesota, Canada, and beyond. @SenTinaSmith and I secured a significant federal grant for the airport to update its taxiway and other infrastructure.

It should be as easy to cancel a subscription as it was to sign up. That’s why the FTC finalized its click-to-cancel rule, and why I will continue to fight for common sense rules of the road to protect consumers from hidden costs, price gouging, and abusive monopolies.

Affordable access to preventive care is an important step toward improving outcomes for breast cancer patients. I’m leading a bipartisan bill with @RogerMarshallMD to enable more women to access screenings and diagnostic exams. https://t.co/Id0QQeXqSr

Far too often, domestic violence survivors face financial or employment challenges after escaping their abusers. I’m co-sponsoring @PattyMurray’s SAFE for Survivors Act to establish protections for survivors so they can have the support they need to rebuild their lives.

St. Cloud Regional Airport is an essential link for residents and businesses in the tri-county region and beyond. @SenTinaSmith and I secured a federal grant for important runway improvements to ensure the airport can continue serving travelers for years to come.

Congratulations to Women’s Advocates on their 50th anniversary of becoming the first domestic violence shelter in the nation. It was a privilege to join them in honoring half a century of service to all who have walked through their doors. https://t.co/ms1ZS1j3wg

We need modern and efficient 9-1-1 systems so all Americans can get the help they need. I’m leading a bipartisan bill to improve the resiliency of our 9-1-1 systems and recognize the critical lifesaving role 9-1-1 dispatchers play.

High-speed internet access is essential for work, school, and more, which is why I fought to secure major federal funding for Minnesota to expand broadband access. @NTIAgov’s approval of our state’s broadband deployment plan brings us closer to closing the digital divide. https://t.co/MlPEZhO8HA

Americans living with disabilities should be able to save for health care expenses, a car, or other needs. That's why I am a co-sponsor of @SenBobCasey’s ENABLE Act, which allows people with disabilities to save and invest without losing access to federal programs like Medicaid.

I recently met with the new @SwissAmbUSA Dr. Ralf Heckner. The U.S. & Switzerland partner on many important issues ranging from national security, trade, & workforce development. As co-chair of the Swiss Caucus, I look forward to forging a stronger bond between our nations.

Investing in sustainable energy is a win-win-win for households, businesses, and our environment. I'll continue working to secure federal funding to build up our clean energy and biofuel sources to power communities and create jobs.
